Paddling around the vicinity of Hickory Island, Black Island, and Mound Key. Mound Key is the site of many shell mounds, and was once the capital of the mighty Calusa people—called Calos. Remains found on Mound Key date back over 2,000 years, it’s thought that this is where the Spaniards first made contact with North American peoples, and you can only access it by boat 🛶 #florida #kayak #mangroves #mounds

Alaskans will know this, but this is a shot of one of our Ghost Forests. Ghost Forests are coastal parts of the forest where salt water from a tsunami caused by the ‘64 earthquake washed up and infiltrated the trees’ root systems. The trees dried & died, but they and their roots still remain intact. I love the ghost forest groves around Girdwood, Prince William Sound, and even the coastline around Seward 😍 #alaska #thealaskalife #52weeksofnature #ghostforest #tsunami #earthquake #blizzard #winter

A snowy harbor. We’ve had multiple feet of snow dumped on us every day for days. This is so reminiscent of winters in my childhood and I just don’t want it to end! #alaska #whittier #thealaskalife #winter #snow
